 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=absolutemaster>Absolute Master</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/13/02 8:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Yyen Level 60 Wizard of Ayonae Ro<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That's the main reason why you will probably not get too many groups in PoV. I think it's more of a level thing then a class thing really. Are level 59's getting groups ahead of you (aside from clerics)? Or maybe it's a rep thing? Wizards are quite desired in PoV groups as damage dealers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>That seems to be the way that several clerics, enchanters and shamans think it should be. I have had a few times where I invite one only to have him say 'Oh, I thought you had a full group&quot; and leave to go lfg again or if I ask if he want to join us he responds 'Do you have an enchanter already?' <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Guilty~. The reasoning behind this is that if you join a partial group and lose the lfg tag, you do not get group invites to already established groups. These partial groups usually just stay at the zone in not doing anything (even if they can kill stuff) and sit on their asses waiting for a healer or a tank and half the time end up disbanding. This means lots of wasted time not exp'ing. Nowadays, if I get asked for a group I always ask them who they have in the group. If it's a new group being started I let him know to give me a tell once he has an established group, but to say that I am part of the group when he recruits for people (more leverage).<br>
<br>
The reason behind the 2nd part is pretty simple (if speaking for enchanters), enchanters don't stack well at all when not in an ae group. If an enchanter is grouped with a higher level enchanter, he can't mez anything because all of his mezzes gets overwritten, or they bounce off mobs because the 2nd enchanter already mezzed them. Same things for buffs. Unless charm fighting or ae is gonna be the focus of the group (specialty groups), pretty much every enchanter will tell you that they do not group with a second enchanter.<br>
<br>
If other classes won't group unless the group has an enchanter, well they are dumb and probably not worth grouping with anyways..<br>
<br>
All that said, I often do create my own groups. Case in point in PoN one time there was 6 or 7 people lfg and not doing anything (they were all /ooc it one after the other which made it funnier). So I shouted out: ranger, monk, cleric, wizard, warrior come to graveyard for group. And the group was made, took 15 seconds.<br>
<br>
It often just takes initiative. If you are lfg, you should actually lfg. I see people too often just sitting at the zoneline, passively /ooc lfg every 5 min or so like if they are botted. Yeah that will get you groups fast, not. Take the initiative and you will get groups. <br>
<br>
Turonyen<br>
Level 65 Enchanter<br>
Tholuxe Paells <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=garrathmoore>Garrath Moore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 447<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/13/02 8:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> My experience with Wizard groupability can be summed up quickly: Those I have grouped with before and those I have not.  <br>
<br>
I have gotten tells from people I have not seen in 3 months and 20 levels asking me to come to PoN, PoD, Chardok etc...When I enter into a zone I have grouped in often, I am normally only LFG for a few minutes. Either someone remembers me (common) and has a spot (rare) or I start rounding up the LFG folk. <br>
<br>
Yes, I shoot for melee/healer/slower/me then the other two, but in PoP you need to have most of those abilities to be successful. Once you have a slower, any tank type class is fine, and any of the healer type classes are fine.  There is nothing wrong with Shaman/SK/Druid/me (wiz)/wiz/other. <br>
<br>
Actually, the best PoI group I have ever been in was exactly that, and we did not even need to fill the 6th spot. We were in one of the junkyards on the left flank, broke the spawn and then just kept moving around the horseshoe until our KEI's and mana ran out, which was a good long while.<br>
<br>
Getting us into groups is more about the class than the player if they dont know you. Group has one more spot for a damage dealer, they taking me (58 wiz) or A_random_rogue01, if they dont know either of us?<br>
<br>
Getting into groups is more about the player than the class when they do know you. The longer you stay in the zone, the more regulars you meet and group with.  Be good at your class and you will not stay LFG for long.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Garrath Moore<br>
