<br>
Sure there are times when you can't find a group. I go quad, work on trade skills or farm for one of my twinks.<br>
<br>
Honestly, I despise pick up groups. There usually full of greedy morons that have no clue how to play the game.<br>
<br>
I usually group with guildies also. I have met quite a lot of people outside my guild that way.<br>
<br>
There are a few people I group with regularly now. I enjoy that the most because we all know who is going to do what in any given situation. ie. Shammy slows and dots I root mob so he stops being pounded on and he knows I will be doing that. He doesn't even have root loaded, so it opens an extra spell slot for him to utilize. Root any adds. And I always protect our healer or anyone who is getting pounded to death even if I die doing it.<br>
<br>
Not to mention blowing the hell out of the mobs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :bounce --><img src=http://graffes.netfirms.com/smiley/bounce.gif ALT=":bounce"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
You just have to find some people that play there class correctly and aren't selfish greedy asswipes and try to make some friends, which can be difficult to find <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Once you do the game really gets fun  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
